# Playnite .NET extensions

Official docs: [Introduction to Playnite extensions](https://playnite.link/docs/tutorials/extensions/intro.html), [Plugins](https://playnite.link/docs/tutorials/extensions/plugins.html).

## Project shape

- In this monorepo, each extension lives under **`src/<PluginName>/`** and is registered in **`src/extensions.json`**.
- Keep extension-owned files together: **`.csproj`**, **`Directory.Build.props`**, **`src/`**, and **`info/extension.yaml`** / installer metadata.
- **Target**: `net462` (or Playnite-supported TFM), **`UseWPF`**: true for UI plugins.
- **PlayniteSDK** NuGet: use **`PrivateAssets=all`** (and typically **`CopyLocalLockFileAssemblies`**: false) unless you have a reason not to.

## extension.yaml

- **`Id`**: stable **AddonId** for life of the add-on; must match **InstallerManifest.yaml** and any **PlayniteAddonDatabase** listing.
- **`Module`**: primary DLL name (e.g. `MyPlugin.dll`).
- **`Type`**: e.g. `GenericPlugin`, `MetadataPlugin`, `LibraryPlugin` — must match base class / SDK expectations.
- **`Version`**: keep in sync with **`Directory.Build.props`** / assembly version and **installer manifest** packages when you ship.

## Logging

- Use **`LogManager.GetLogger()`** from **Playnite.SDK**. Do not assume **`IPlayniteAPI.CreateLogger`** exists.

## UI thread and WPF

- Touch the visual tree, **MainWindow**, or controls from **`PlayniteApi.MainView.UIDispatcher`** (e.g. `BeginInvoke` with appropriate priority).
- Gate behavior by view when relevant (**`DesktopView`**, Fullscreen, etc.) using **`PlayniteApi.MainView.ActiveDesktopView`** (or the API your scenario needs).

## Settings

- Implement **`ISettings`** with **`BeginEdit`**, **`CancelEdit`**, **`EndEdit`**; persist via **`SavePluginSettings`** on the plugin instance.
- Use **`VerifySettings`** for validation messages.
- Settings **UserControl** returned from **`GetSettingsView`** should bind to the same settings object the plugin uses.

## Reflection and Playnite internals

- Prefer public APIs; if you reflect into Playnite or **`AppSettings`**, expect breakage on Playnite upgrades. Use a **clear disable path** (e.g. a `reflectionBroken` flag) and log once rather than spamming exceptions.

## Runtime testing

- **Plugins are not hot-reloaded**: replace **`*.dll`** then **restart Playnite** to verify changes.
- Test both **Desktop** and **Fullscreen** if the feature applies to both.

## Shipping (overview)

- Use **`scripts/validate-extension.ps1 -Extension <key>`** before shipping.
- See repo **`README.md`** (Publish / Release) and skill **`playnite-extension-release`** for **Toolbox** **`.pext`**, per-extension **`InstallerManifest.yaml`**, and **PlayniteAddonDatabase**.
